The '''Croatian Heritage Foundation''' ({{lang-hr|Hrvatska matica isljenika}}) is an organization which works with [[Croatia]]n [[emigrants]]. It helps connect [[diaspora]] groups back to the country. The foundation organizes several programs within Croatia and around the world ranging from language to folklore. It publishes its own monthly magazine, ''Matica'',<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.matis.hr/index.php/en/activities/publishing/matica-monthly-magazine | title=Matica-monthly magazine | publisher=Croatian Heritage Foundation | work=matis.hr | accessdate=24 September 2012}}</ref> as well as the ''Croatian Emigrant Almanac'' ({{lang|hr|Hrvatski iseljenički zbornik}}), printed in Croatian, English and Spanish.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.matis.hr/index.php/en/activities/publishing/croatian-emigrant-almanac | title=The Croatian Emigrant Almanac | publisher=Croatian Heritage Foundation | work=matis.hr | accessdate=24 September 2012}}</ref>
A large part of the foundation's work deals with preventing the assimilation of diaspora Croats into other cultures. This is significant because of the relatively large population of Croats living outside of the country. The CHF runs branches in [[Pula]], [[Rijeka]], [[Zadar]], [[Split (city)|Split]], [[Dubrovnik]] and [[Vukovar]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.matis.hr/index.php/en/about-us/constitution | title=Constitution | publisher=Croatian Heritage Foundation | work=matis.hr | accessdate=24 September 2012}}</ref>
Its {{as of|2012|alt=current}} director is Marin Knezović.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.matis.hr/index.php/en/about-us/mission | title=Mission | publisher=Croatian Heritage Foundation | work=matis.hr | accessdate=24 September 2012}}</ref>
